{
  "id": 5199437611794432,
  "name": "WebGPU: Immediates",
  "summary": "Functionality added to the WebGPU spec after its first shipment in a browser.\n\nAdds a new immediate address space in WGSL and a setImmediateData() method on render pass, compute pass, and render bundle encoders that allows passing small amounts of frequently-updated data directly to shaders without creating GPU buffer objects or bind groups. This is particularly useful for applications that need to update per-draw parameters such as object indices, material indices, or transformation matrices every draw call, enabling significant performance improvements by avoiding buffer and bind group management overhead.",
